<inglise> ARTICLE 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The Treaty on European Union shall be amended in accordance with the provisions of this Article. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt k&auml;esoleva artikli s&auml;tetele muudetakse Euroopa Liidu lepingut. </eesti>
<inglise> 1) After the third recital the following recital shall be inserted: </inglise>
<eesti> 1) Preambuli kolmanda l&otilde;igu j&auml;rele lisatakse j&auml;rgmine l&otilde;ik: </eesti>
<inglise> "CONFIRMING their attachment to fundamental social rights as defined in the European Social Charter signed at Turin on 18 October 1961 and in the 1989 Community Charter of the Fundamental Social Rights of Workers," </inglise>
<eesti> "KINNITADES oma ustavust sotsiaalsetele p&otilde;hi&otilde;igustele, nagu need on m&auml;&auml;ratletud 18. oktoobril 1961 Torinos allakirjutatud Euroopa sotsiaalhartas ja &uuml;henduse 1989. aasta hartas t&ouml;&ouml;tajate sotsiaalsete p&otilde;hi&otilde;iguste kohta". </eesti>
<inglise> 2) The existing seventh recital shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> 2) Senine seitsmes l&otilde;ik asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "DETERMINED to promote economic and social progress for their peoples, taking into account the principle of sustainable development and within the context of the accomplishment of the internal market and of reinforced cohesion and environmental protection, and to implement policies ensuring that advances in economic integration are accompanied by parallel progress in other fields," </inglise>
<eesti> "OTSUSTANUD seoses siseturu v&auml;ljakujundamise ning &uuml;htekuuluvuse ja keskkonnakaitse tugevdamisega ja s&auml;&auml;stva arengu p&otilde;him&otilde;tet j&auml;rgides eden/dada oma rahvaste majanduslikku ja sotsiaalset progressi ning rakendada poliitikat, mis tagaks, et majandusliku integratsiooni edusammudega kaasneks r&ouml;&ouml;bitine progress muudes valdkondades". </eesti>
<inglise> 3) The existing ninth and tenth recitals shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> 3) Senised &uuml;heksas ja k&uuml;mnes l&otilde;ik asendatakse j&auml;rgmistega: </eesti>
<inglise> "RESOLVED to implement a common foreign and security policy including the progressive framing of a common defence policy, which might lead to a common defence in accordance with the provisions of Article J.7, thereby reinforcing the European identity and its independence in order to promote peace, security and progress in Europe and in the world, </inglise>
<eesti> "OTSUSTANUD rakendada &uuml;hist v&auml;lis- ja julgeolekupoliitikat, mis h&otilde;lmab j&auml;rk-j&auml;rgult kujundatavat &uuml;hist kaitsepoliitikat, mis vastavalt artikli J.7 s&auml;tetele v&otilde;ib viia &uuml;hiskaitseni, ning niiviisi tugevdada Euroopa identiteeti ja s&otilde;ltumatust rahu, julgeoleku ja progressi soodustamiseks Euroopas ja kogu maailmas, </eesti>
<inglise> RESOLVED to facilitate the free movement of persons, while ensuring the safety and security of their peoples, by establishing an area of freedom, security and justice, in accordance with the provisions of this Treaty," </inglise>
<eesti> OTSUSTANUD h&otilde;lbustada isikute vaba liikumist, samal ajal tagades oma rahvaste ohutuse ja julgeoleku, luues koosk&otilde;las k&auml;esoleva lepingu s&auml;tetega vabadusel, turvalisusel ja &otilde;igusel rajaneva ala". </eesti>
<inglise> 4) In Article A the second paragraph shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> 4) Artiklis A asendatakse teine l&otilde;ik j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "This Treaty marks a new stage in the process of creating an ever closer union among the peoples of Europe, in which decisions are taken as openly as possible and as closely as possible to the citizen." </inglise>
<eesti> "K&auml;esolev leping t&auml;histab uut etappi Euroopa rahvaste &uuml;ha tihedama liidu loomises, kus otsused tehakse nii avalikult kui v&otilde;imalik ja nii kodanikul&auml;hedaselt kui v&otilde;imalik." </eesti>
<inglise> 5) Article B shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> 5) Artikkel B asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "Article B </inglise>
<eesti> "Artikkel B </eesti>
<inglise> The Union shall set itself the following objectives: </inglise>
<eesti> Liit seab endale j&auml;rgmised eesm&auml;rgid: </eesti>
<inglise> - to promote economic and social progress and a high level of employment and to achieve balanced and sustainable development, in particular through the creation of an area without internal frontiers, through the strengthening of economic and social cohesion and through the establishment of economic and monetary union, ultimately including a single currency in accordance with the provisions of this Treaty; </inglise>
<eesti> - edendada majanduslikku ja sotsiaalset progressi, k&otilde;rget t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ive taset ning saavutada tasakaalustatud ja p&uuml;siv areng, eriti sisepiirideta ala loomise, majandusliku ja sotsiaalse &uuml;htekuuluvuse tugevdamise ning k&auml;esoleva lepingu s&auml;tete kohaselt l&otilde;pptulemusena &uuml;hisraha h&otilde;lmava majandus- ja rahaliidu loomise kaudu; </eesti>
<inglise> - to assert its identity on the international scene, in particular through the implementation of a common foreign and security policy including the progressive framing of a common defence policy, which might lead to a common defence, in accordance with the provisions of Article J.7; </inglise>
<eesti> - kinnitada oma identiteeti rahvusvahelisel tasandil eelk&otilde;ige &uuml;hise v&auml;lis- ja julgeolekupoliitika rakendamise kaudu, kaasa arvatud &uuml;hise kaitsepoliitika j&auml;rkj&auml;rguline kujundamine, mis vastavalt artikli J.7 s&auml;tetele v&otilde;ib viia &uuml;hiskaitseni; </eesti>
<inglise> - to strengthen the protection of the rights and interests of the nationals of its Member States through the introduction of a citizenship of the Union; </inglise>
<eesti> - tugevdada liikmesriikide kodanike &otilde;iguste ja huvide kaitset liidu kodakondsuse sisseseadmise kaudu; </eesti>
<inglise> - to maintain and develop the Union as an area of freedom, security and justice, in which the free movement of persons is assured in conjunction with appropriate measures with respect to external border controls, asylum, immigration and the prevention and combating of crime; </inglise>
<eesti> - s&auml;ilitada ja arendada liitu vabadusel, turvalisusel ja &otilde;igusel rajaneva alana, kus isikute vaba liikumine on tagatud &uuml;heskoos nii v&auml;lispiirikontrolli, varjupaiga ja sisser&auml;ndega kui ka kuritegevuse ennetamise ja selle vastu v&otilde;itlemisega seotud asjakohaste meetmete v&otilde;tmisega; </eesti>
<inglise> - to maintain in full the acquis communautaire and build on it with a view to considering to what extent the policies and forms of cooperation introduced by this Treaty may need to be revised with the aim of ensuring the effectiveness of the mechanisms and the institutions of the Community. </inglise>
<eesti> - s&auml;ilitada t&auml;iel m&auml;&auml;ral acquis communautaire ja arendada seda edasi, silmas pidades, mil m&auml;&auml;ral k&auml;esoleva lepingu alusel kasutuselev&otilde;etud poliitika ja koost&ouml;&ouml;vormid v&otilde;iksid vajada revideerimist, selleks et tagada &uuml;henduse mehhanismide ja institutsioonide t&otilde;husus. </eesti>
<inglise> The objectives of the Union shall be achieved as provided in this Treaty and in accordance with the conditions and the timetable set out therein while respecting the principle of subsidiarity as defined in Article 3b of the Treaty establishing the European Community." </inglise>
<eesti> Liidu eesm&auml;rgid saavutatakse k&auml;esoleva lepingu kohaselt ning koosk&otilde;las lepingus esitatud tingimuste ja ajakavaga, &uuml;htlasi kinni pidades subsidiaarsuse p&otilde;him&otilde;ttest, nagu see on m&auml;&auml;ratletud Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingu artiklis 3b." </eesti>
<inglise> 6) In Article C, the second paragraph shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> 6) Artiklis C asendatakse teine l&otilde;ik j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "The Union shall in particular ensure the consistency of its external activities as a whole in the context of its external relations, security, economic and development policies. </inglise>
<eesti> "Eelk&otilde;ige tagab liit oma v&auml;listegevuse kui terviku j&auml;rjepidevuse liidu v&auml;lissuhete, julgeoleku-, majandus- ja arengupoliitika raames. </eesti>
<inglise> The Council and the Commission shall be responsible for ensuring such consistency and shall cooperate to this end. They shall ensure the implementation of these policies, each in accordance with its respective powers." </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu ja komisjon vastutavad nimetatud j&auml;rjepidevuse tagamise eest ja teevad sel eesm&auml;rgil koost&ouml;&ouml;d. Nad tagavad asjaomase poliitika elluviimise vastavalt oma volitustele." </eesti>
<inglise> 7) Article E shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> 7) Artikkel E asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "Article E </inglise>
<eesti> "Artikkel E </eesti>
<inglise> The European Parliament, the Council, the Commission, the Court of Justice and the Court of Auditors shall exercise their powers under the conditions and for the purposes provided for, on the one hand, by the provisions of the Treaties establishing the European Communities and of the subsequent Treaties and Acts modifying and supplementing them and, on the other hand, by the other provisions of this Treaty." </inglise>
<eesti> Euroopa Parlament, n&otilde;ukogu, komisjon, kohus ja kontrollikoda kasutavad oma volitusi koosk&otilde;las nende tingimuste ja eesm&auml;rkidega, mis on ette n&auml;htud &uuml;helt poolt Euroopa &uuml;henduste asutamislepingute ning neid muutvate ja t&auml;iendavate hilisemate lepingute ja aktide s&auml;tetega ning teiselt poolt k&auml;esoleva lepingu &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;nud s&auml;tetega." </eesti>
<inglise> 8) Article F shall be amended as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> 8) Artiklit F muudetakse j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) paragraph 1 shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> a) l&otilde;ige 1 asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "1. </inglise>
<eesti> "1. </eesti>
<inglise> The Union is founded on the principles of liberty, democracy, respect for human rights and fundamental freedoms, and the rule of law, principles which are common to the Member States. &ldquo;; </inglise>
<eesti> Liit on rajatud vabaduse, demokraatia, inim&otilde;iguste ja p&otilde;hivabaduste austamise ning &otilde;igusriigi p&otilde;him&otilde;tetele, mis on &uuml;hised k&otilde;ikidele liikmesriikidele"; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the existing paragraph 3 shall become paragraph 4 and a new paragraph 3 shall be inserted as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> b) senine 3 l&otilde;ige muutub l&otilde;ikeks 4 ja lisatakse j&auml;rgmine uus l&otilde;ige 3: </eesti>
<inglise> "3. </inglise>
<eesti> "3. </eesti>
<inglise> The Union shall respect the national identities of its Member States." </inglise>
<eesti> Liit austab liikmesriikide rahvuslikku omap&auml;ra". </eesti>
<inglise> 9) The following Article shall be inserted at the end of Title I: </inglise>
<eesti> 9) I jaotise l&otilde;ppu lisatakse j&auml;rgmine artikkel: </eesti>
<inglise> "Article F.1 </inglise>
<eesti> "Artikkel F.1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The Council, meeting in the composition of the Heads of State or Government and acting by unanimity on a proposal by one third of the Member States or by the Commission and after obtaining the assent of the European Parliament, may determine the existence of a serious and persistent breach by a Member State of principles mentioned in Article F(1), after inviting the government of the Member State in question to submit its observations. </inglise>
<eesti> Riigipeade ja valitsusjuhtide tasandil kokku tulev n&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;ib &uuml;he kolmandiku liikmesriikide v&otilde;i komisjoni ettepaneku p&otilde;hjal ning p&auml;rast Euroopa Parlamendilt n&otilde;usoleku saamist teha &uuml;heh&auml;&auml;lselt kindlaks, et m&otilde;ni liikmesriik rikub raskelt ja j&auml;tkuvalt artikli F l&otilde;ikes 1 mainitud p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid, olles enne seda kutsunud k&otilde;nealuse liikmesriigi valitsust &uuml;les esitama oma seisukohta. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Where such a determination has been made, the Council, acting by a qualified majority, may decide to suspend certain of the rights deriving from the application of this Treaty to the Member State in question, including the voting rights of the representative of the government of that Member State in the Council. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui selline rikkumine on kindlaks tehtud, v&otilde;ib n&otilde;ukogu kvalifitseeritud h&auml;&auml;lteenamusega teha otsuse peatada teatavad &otilde;igused, mis tulenevad k&auml;esoleva lepingu kohaldamisest k&otilde;nealuse liikmesriigi suhtes, sealhulgas peatada selle liikmesriigi valitsuse esindaja h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;iguse n&otilde;ukogus. </eesti>
<inglise> In doing so, the Council shall take into account the possible consequences of such a suspension on the rights and obligations of natural and legal persons. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda tehes v&otilde;tab n&otilde;ukogu arvesse sellise peatamise v&otilde;imalikke tagaj&auml;rgi f&uuml;&uuml;siliste ja juriidiliste isikute &otilde;igustele ja kohustustele. </eesti>
<inglise> The obligations of the Member State in question under this Treaty shall in any case continue to be binding on that State. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealuse liikmesriigi k&auml;esoleva lepingu j&auml;rgsed kohustused on sellele riigile j&auml;tkuvalt siduvad. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The Council, acting by a qualified majority, may decide subsequently to vary or revoke measures taken under paragraph 2 in response to changes in the situation which led to their being imposed. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;ib kvalifitseeritud h&auml;&auml;lteenamusega teha hiljem otsuse l&otilde;ike 2 alusel v&otilde;etud meetmeid muuta v&otilde;i need t&uuml;histada, kui nende kehtestamise tinginud olukord muutub. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Article, the Council shall act without taking into account the vote of the representative of the government of the Member State in question. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva artikli kohaldamisel teeb n&otilde;ukogu otsuseid k&otilde;nealuse liikmesriigi valitsuse esindaja h&auml;&auml;lt arvestamata. </eesti>
<inglise> Abstentions by members present in person or represented shall not prevent the adoption of decisions referred to in paragraph 1. </inglise>
